WEBVTT

00:00:09.197 --> 00:00:11.825
VIETNAM, 1965

00:00:31.470 --> 00:00:32.471
Column, halt.

00:00:42.564 --> 00:00:46.109
It doesn't really matter
what the war is for.

00:00:52.532 --> 00:00:56.453
Someone's death becomes
someone else's chance.

00:00:57.913 --> 00:00:59.122
That's what war is.

00:01:19.643 --> 00:01:21.645
Looks like one of the Vietcong tunnels.

00:01:44.751 --> 00:01:45.836
Moving in.

00:02:20.078 --> 00:02:23.582
And my role was to be that death.

00:02:24.750 --> 00:02:27.753
Just cannon fodder
for someone else's rise.

00:03:26.228 --> 00:03:28.688
- How did it go?
- It's been taken care of, sir.

00:03:29.856 --> 00:03:31.191
And the money in the safe?

00:03:31.274 --> 00:03:33.026
Baek will take it to you.

00:03:33.944 --> 00:03:36.363
Clean it up right. No loose ends.

00:03:36.446 --> 00:03:37.531
Yes, sir. Understood.

00:03:56.633 --> 00:03:57.676
It's done. (Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org)

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:07.060
Mr. Jang!

00:04:07.727 --> 00:04:11.356
Man, what the hell happened here?

00:04:12.232 --> 00:04:14.901
Mr. Jang, are you all right? Are you hurt?

00:04:16.194 --> 00:04:20.115
-Baek Kitae didn't show, right?
-No, he never got off the ship.

00:04:22.659 --> 00:04:26.538
Well, let's start by tracking down
Pyo Haksu first.

00:04:26.621 --> 00:04:29.958
We were just about to call in backup
from the nearby army base.

00:04:31.042 --> 00:04:34.129
Search request,
KCIA Agent Pyo Haksu.

00:04:34.212 --> 00:04:36.882
- He showed up on his own.
- You can't come in here!

00:04:37.465 --> 00:04:39.009
Move, asshole. I'm with the KCIA.

00:04:39.092 --> 00:04:41.344
- Hey! Let him through.
- I said, move!

00:04:44.014 --> 00:04:45.140
Mr. Pyo Haksu!

00:04:48.727 --> 00:04:49.895
Come here, please.

00:04:51.021 --> 00:04:52.397
How do you know who I am?

00:04:53.815 --> 00:04:55.108
What's going on here?

00:04:55.191 --> 00:04:57.611
I'm Busan District Prosecutor
Jang Geonyoung.

00:04:58.278 --> 00:04:59.279
Okay. And?

00:04:59.779 --> 00:05:02.490
What brings the KCIA department head here?

00:05:03.074 --> 00:05:04.826
I came to pick up the director.

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:07.662
- Director Hwang?
- Yes, where is he?

00:05:07.746 --> 00:05:08.955
Well, you killed him.

00:05:10.582 --> 00:05:11.958
You're under arrest

00:05:12.042 --> 00:05:15.545
for suspicion of Director General
Hwang Gukpyeong's murder.

00:05:16.296 --> 00:05:17.297
Cuff him.

00:05:18.256 --> 00:05:19.466
Don't be ridiculous.

00:05:19.549 --> 00:05:20.926
- Hey, wait.
- Don't make a scene.

00:05:21.009 --> 00:05:22.177
-Just hold on.
-Come on.

00:05:22.886 --> 00:05:25.013
No, stop! I'll do it myself.

00:05:29.059 --> 00:05:31.853
You sure you can handle this?
What do you think you're doing?

00:05:31.937 --> 00:05:33.521
Quiet down. Let's go.

00:05:34.689 --> 00:05:36.858
WAR OF BLOOD

00:05:43.865 --> 00:05:45.283
Mr. Baek, you're here.

00:05:48.036 --> 00:05:49.079
What's going on?

00:05:49.162 --> 00:05:50.580
Prosecutors arrested Mr. Pyo

00:05:50.664 --> 00:05:52.832
under suspicion
of murdering Director Hwang.

00:05:52.916 --> 00:05:56.711
We're waiting on the autopsy to confirm
the body's really Director Hwang.

00:05:57.462 --> 00:05:58.672
Silence the press first.

00:05:58.755 --> 00:05:59.756
Yes, sir.

00:06:01.299 --> 00:06:03.551
Wait, sir. There's blood on your…

00:06:09.599 --> 00:06:11.685
I'm heading up to Seoul.
Get the car ready.

00:06:11.768 --> 00:06:13.019
Yes, sir.

00:07:03.778 --> 00:07:04.904
Hello?

00:07:04.988 --> 00:07:07.157
- Hey, Soyeong.
- Hi, Kitae.

00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:09.659
- Where's Daeil now?
- Mr. Daeil?

00:07:10.368 --> 00:07:12.912
He was at the lab
but left to take care of something.

00:07:13.413 --> 00:07:14.456
Why do you ask?

00:07:15.540 --> 00:07:18.084
-Is something wrong?
-Got it. I have to go.

00:07:21.337 --> 00:07:22.338
Who was that?

00:07:23.715 --> 00:07:25.341
It's Kitae. He's looking for you.

00:07:27.051 --> 00:07:28.052
What for?

00:07:30.597 --> 00:07:31.806
I have no idea.

00:07:32.348 --> 00:07:35.685
Mr. Pyo Haksu.

00:07:38.104 --> 00:07:39.272
Why did you kill him?

00:07:39.939 --> 00:07:41.107
Why did you kill Hwang?

00:07:41.608 --> 00:07:42.984
You keep crossing the line.

00:07:43.651 --> 00:07:45.528
If you keep bulldozing ahead like that,

00:07:45.612 --> 00:07:47.947
how will you handle
the consequences later?

00:07:48.031 --> 00:07:49.324
Just worried about you.

00:07:52.285 --> 00:07:53.620
You killed him. Didn't you?

00:07:55.038 --> 00:07:56.039
Did you see it?

00:07:56.122 --> 00:07:59.459
I saw him dead, shot through the eye.

00:07:59.542 --> 00:08:02.378
I told you. I dropped him off
and went to buy cigarettes.

00:08:02.462 --> 00:08:04.881
Go ask at the store.
How many times do I have to…

00:08:07.759 --> 00:08:11.179
So you're saying,
while you were out buying cigarettes,

00:08:12.931 --> 00:08:14.390
Hwang ended up dead?

00:08:14.474 --> 00:08:16.476
What then?

00:08:17.519 --> 00:08:19.229
You think I killed him

00:08:20.104 --> 00:08:21.773
and then went out for cigarettes?

00:08:22.732 --> 00:08:24.484
And the fire just happened to break out?

00:08:24.567 --> 00:08:26.903
Come on, Mr. Jang. That doesn't add up.

00:08:26.986 --> 00:08:29.447
And what motive could I have to kill him?

00:08:30.615 --> 00:08:31.783
There's no motive.

00:08:32.492 --> 00:08:33.493
Right.

00:08:35.161 --> 00:08:39.958
You went to buy cigarettes,
Hwang died, and the fire broke out.

00:08:40.625 --> 00:08:42.377
Baek Kitae was with you, wasn't he?

00:08:44.587 --> 00:08:47.674
He was with you at the temple, right?

00:09:29.799 --> 00:09:30.800
Here it is.

00:09:30.884 --> 00:09:32.677
Look, that's Ikeda Yuji.

00:09:33.678 --> 00:09:35.555
Tell me, what was the KCIA

00:09:36.306 --> 00:09:38.433
doing with the yakuza in Osaka?

00:09:39.350 --> 00:09:42.395
That's classified. I can't tell you.

00:09:42.478 --> 00:09:44.647
Classified, my fucking ass.

00:09:44.731 --> 00:09:46.024
Watch your language.

00:09:46.107 --> 00:09:48.359
I know you and Baek Kitae went to Japan

00:09:48.943 --> 00:09:50.361
and sold meth there.

00:09:50.445 --> 00:09:53.364
Then, you passed the money to Hwang.

00:09:55.033 --> 00:09:57.327
You did all the work,

00:09:57.410 --> 00:09:59.287
but the bastard reaped the cash.

00:09:59.370 --> 00:10:04.000
That's why you and Baek Kitae
killed him, isn't it?

00:10:06.628 --> 00:10:08.254
Do you have proof? Do you?

00:10:08.338 --> 00:10:11.299
Proof? Sure.
I'll whip up a good one for you.

00:10:11.382 --> 00:10:13.134
- Wow.
- You little…

00:10:13.218 --> 00:10:14.302
You do that.

00:10:14.385 --> 00:10:15.386
Hey.

00:10:16.387 --> 00:10:18.431
You like prison food? Huh?

00:10:22.936 --> 00:10:24.395
- Jang.
- Yes?

00:10:24.479 --> 00:10:25.813
A word?

00:10:25.897 --> 00:10:27.774
Goodness! What is it?

00:10:27.857 --> 00:10:29.234
You should go.

00:10:29.317 --> 00:10:33.029
- Looks like you're in trouble. Go on.
- Have a smoke while I'm gone.

00:10:47.335 --> 00:10:48.962
Geez.

00:10:51.839 --> 00:10:54.842
BUSAN DISTRICT
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE CASE RECORDS

00:10:57.262 --> 00:10:58.846
So, Baek Kitae took over

00:10:59.889 --> 00:11:01.474
Jo Manjae's meth business?

00:11:02.225 --> 00:11:03.226
Yes, sir.

00:11:03.309 --> 00:11:05.561
With Kang Daeil backing him?

00:11:05.645 --> 00:11:06.646
That's right.

00:11:08.982 --> 00:11:10.400
And they killed Director Hwang?

00:11:10.984 --> 00:11:12.610
He had a gunshot wound

00:11:13.778 --> 00:11:14.988
to the face,

00:11:15.530 --> 00:11:17.865
through the right eye.

00:11:19.158 --> 00:11:20.618
They shot him dead.

00:11:21.661 --> 00:11:23.538
And set the place on fire

00:11:23.621 --> 00:11:25.415
to wipe out the evidence.

00:11:28.918 --> 00:11:29.919
Sir.

00:11:30.503 --> 00:11:31.504
I'm going to

00:11:32.046 --> 00:11:33.881
issue an arrest warrant for Baek Kitae.

00:11:33.965 --> 00:11:35.300
If this goes wrong,

00:11:36.175 --> 00:11:38.011
the whole prosecution blows up.

00:11:38.970 --> 00:11:39.971
You realize that?

00:11:40.638 --> 00:11:42.473
-Yes.
-Fucking hell.

00:11:43.016 --> 00:11:46.060
I'll make sure we get Pyo's confession.

00:11:51.190 --> 00:11:52.483
This is the money

00:11:52.567 --> 00:11:55.028
Director Hwang had been skimming off
behind your back.

00:11:57.447 --> 00:12:00.825
Looks like his head wasn't the only thing
he was thinning out.

00:12:01.451 --> 00:12:04.912
I believe he also had some land
and buildings in his relatives' names.

00:12:04.996 --> 00:12:07.373
I'll check and report back
as soon as I can.

00:12:10.501 --> 00:12:11.753
And this.

00:12:27.018 --> 00:12:28.686
It's Bae Geumji's notebook.

00:12:35.485 --> 00:12:36.486
Did you look?

00:12:36.986 --> 00:12:37.987
Yes, sir.

00:12:38.571 --> 00:12:39.822
I did.

00:12:42.033 --> 00:12:43.034
And you saw my name?

00:12:43.743 --> 00:12:44.744
I'm sorry, sir.

00:12:56.506 --> 00:12:57.840
What do you want?

00:12:59.008 --> 00:13:02.595
I came to ask you
to please reinvest this money with me.

00:13:04.889 --> 00:13:07.975
If you'd let me,
I'm sure I can use this as seed money

00:13:08.059 --> 00:13:10.269
and multiply the returns
by many times over.

00:13:11.229 --> 00:13:12.605
So you're saying,

00:13:13.773 --> 00:13:15.400
you want to do business with me?

00:13:15.900 --> 00:13:17.652
The election is less than a year away.

00:13:17.735 --> 00:13:19.654
I heard the President needs 70 billion won

00:13:19.737 --> 00:13:22.156
to secure another term
for the good of the nation.

00:13:23.741 --> 00:13:24.951
I'll raise it.

00:13:26.452 --> 00:13:27.995
How can I trust you?

00:13:28.079 --> 00:13:29.455
You don't have to trust me.

00:13:29.539 --> 00:13:32.166
Just give me a chance
to prove what I can do.

00:13:32.667 --> 00:13:36.295
I'll show you that even if you don't
trust me, you can trust my money.

00:13:37.630 --> 00:13:39.340
I won't let you down, sir.

00:13:59.527 --> 00:14:00.820
Go sit in that chair.

00:14:10.288 --> 00:14:11.622
Go sit in it.

00:14:30.391 --> 00:14:32.768
I heard Hwang went around
telling everyone

00:14:32.852 --> 00:14:34.562
you were his pick for the next director,

00:14:34.645 --> 00:14:37.481
and he took good care of you.

00:14:43.404 --> 00:14:45.990
And that made a lot of people jealous.

00:14:51.454 --> 00:14:52.455
Now that…

00:14:54.373 --> 00:14:56.167
he's dead…

00:14:58.294 --> 00:15:00.421
shouldn't you be
the one to take his place?

00:15:04.175 --> 00:15:05.551
Come to think of it,

00:15:06.135 --> 00:15:07.720
it's not all bad

00:15:08.387 --> 00:15:11.307
for Baek Kitae that you're stuck in here.

00:15:12.225 --> 00:15:14.560
Someone definitely murdered Hwang

00:15:14.644 --> 00:15:16.437
with a gun and burned down the place…

00:15:19.398 --> 00:15:21.150
but you were out buying cigarettes.

00:15:25.196 --> 00:15:27.073
Do you trust Baek Kitae?

00:15:28.491 --> 00:15:31.744
I don't know what kind of deal
you made with him,

00:15:31.827 --> 00:15:33.371
but think carefully.

00:15:35.248 --> 00:15:37.833
You and I both know

00:15:38.793 --> 00:15:40.169
who killed Hwang.

00:15:49.553 --> 00:15:50.554
PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:15:50.638 --> 00:15:51.847
STATEMENT

00:15:53.099 --> 00:15:54.100
That day,

00:15:55.726 --> 00:15:56.894
who else

00:15:58.187 --> 00:15:59.647
was at that temple…

00:16:03.401 --> 00:16:05.027
besides Hwang?

00:16:05.111 --> 00:16:06.320
I want you to write down

00:16:08.072 --> 00:16:09.448
the truth.

00:16:12.368 --> 00:16:14.370
Do you want to rot in prison?

00:16:22.753 --> 00:16:25.840
Baek Kitae becomes director general,

00:16:27.174 --> 00:16:30.177
and you go to prison.

00:16:36.767 --> 00:16:38.853
- Excuse me, sir.
- Yes?

00:16:38.936 --> 00:16:39.979
Damn it.

00:16:40.062 --> 00:16:41.355
What's going on?

00:16:41.439 --> 00:16:45.192
The deputy chief prosecutor ordered
the release of Pyo Haksu.

00:16:45.776 --> 00:16:47.320
Please come with us, Mr. Pyo.

00:17:01.667 --> 00:17:02.668
God, my legs…

00:17:09.550 --> 00:17:10.843
Mr. Seo!

00:17:11.927 --> 00:17:13.012
Mr. Seo!

00:17:13.596 --> 00:17:16.307
How can the prosecution hand over
its investigative authority?

00:17:16.390 --> 00:17:17.641
To the suspects, no less!

00:17:18.642 --> 00:17:19.894
Who says you can do that?

00:17:21.062 --> 00:17:22.063
Hey!

00:17:25.399 --> 00:17:27.360
Get back inside.

00:17:27.443 --> 00:17:29.153
You too. Get back inside.

00:17:29.236 --> 00:17:32.657
DEPUTY CHIEF PROSECUTOR'S OFFICE
PROSECUTOR SEO GIHO

00:17:32.740 --> 00:17:33.908
What about you?

00:17:33.991 --> 00:17:36.369
Who says they're suspects?
You have no evidence.

00:17:37.078 --> 00:17:39.538
You said you didn't see Baek Kitae there.

00:17:39.622 --> 00:17:41.540
I'll arrest him on meth charges first.

00:17:42.583 --> 00:17:46.420
I'll get Kang Daeil to talk,
charge Baek with drug offenses,

00:17:46.921 --> 00:17:50.049
and then prove the murder!

00:17:50.132 --> 00:17:52.051
Now's the time to keep your head down.

00:17:52.134 --> 00:17:53.928
They've even stripped our authority.

00:17:54.428 --> 00:17:57.598
You've got to hold on to your job
if you want another chance later.

00:17:58.974 --> 00:18:02.395
That bastard
killed his own boss just to push meth!

00:18:02.895 --> 00:18:04.105
All right?

00:18:04.188 --> 00:18:07.650
You know if we don't get him now,
he'll become too big to catch!

00:18:09.068 --> 00:18:11.737
The order came from much higher up.

00:18:12.571 --> 00:18:14.156
You understand what I'm saying?

00:18:14.240 --> 00:18:16.701
Well, who the hell is this higher-up?

00:18:19.453 --> 00:18:21.122
Just watch your back for a while.

00:18:23.999 --> 00:18:27.128
THE BLUE HOUSE
REPUBLIC OF KOREA

00:18:36.053 --> 00:18:40.141
Na's really getting under
Cheon's skin today, huh?

00:18:40.224 --> 00:18:41.392
Tell me about it.

00:18:41.475 --> 00:18:43.686
The President favors
Cheon of the Security Service

00:18:43.769 --> 00:18:45.688
over the secretariat these days, so…

00:18:50.693 --> 00:18:51.694
Mr. Na.

00:18:52.570 --> 00:18:55.740
Why do you keep stirring up
something that's already settled?

00:18:55.823 --> 00:18:57.199
Didn't you hear me?

00:18:57.283 --> 00:18:58.659
It was the President's orders.

00:18:58.743 --> 00:19:00.745
That's what you always say.

00:19:02.121 --> 00:19:04.081
It's getting hard to believe.

00:19:04.165 --> 00:19:07.460
If you don't believe me,
go ahead and check with him yourself.

00:19:09.670 --> 00:19:13.924
Still, I serve him the same way you do,
so how could you do that without a word--

00:19:14.008 --> 00:19:17.762
Did you ask me
before getting rid of Bae Geumji?

00:19:19.513 --> 00:19:21.891
You've got to be joking.

00:19:23.726 --> 00:19:25.853
- Bae Geumji? Me?
- Anyway…

00:19:26.437 --> 00:19:29.231
Keep tossing people out for no reason,

00:19:29.315 --> 00:19:31.776
and you might be the next one to go.

00:19:32.777 --> 00:19:33.778
All right?

00:19:34.445 --> 00:19:38.616
You know, I'm just saying this
for your own good.

00:19:39.909 --> 00:19:41.035
Right, of course.

00:19:43.078 --> 00:19:45.706
Since you're so concerned,
I'll bear that in mind.

00:19:47.082 --> 00:19:48.083
Oh, right.

00:19:48.167 --> 00:19:50.711
I heard you lost one of your subordinates.

00:19:50.795 --> 00:19:52.755
You must be devastated.

00:19:53.464 --> 00:19:54.924
Perhaps, it's a sign

00:19:55.633 --> 00:19:58.552
you should watch your back too, Mr. Cheon.

00:20:04.975 --> 00:20:08.354
Yeah,
you should always be careful too.

00:20:09.939 --> 00:20:11.899
Take care of yourself.

00:20:14.819 --> 00:20:17.196
As you know, I don't ask anyone…

00:20:19.949 --> 00:20:21.700
before I get rid of someone.

00:20:25.454 --> 00:20:27.581
It looks like there's a leak.

00:20:28.374 --> 00:20:29.875
Any idea who?

00:20:32.294 --> 00:20:35.089
Jang Geonyoung knew we went to Japan.

00:20:35.714 --> 00:20:37.424
And what we went there for.

00:20:39.802 --> 00:20:41.053
So what did you tell him?

00:20:41.136 --> 00:20:43.514
Well, what else?
I said it was classified.

00:20:45.766 --> 00:20:47.142
Did he say anything else?

00:20:47.226 --> 00:20:49.603
He was sure you're the one
who killed Hwang.

00:20:56.277 --> 00:20:58.028
How did your meeting with Cheon go?

00:21:03.284 --> 00:21:04.869
How much…

00:21:06.745 --> 00:21:08.372
did you tell Cheon?

00:21:09.039 --> 00:21:10.207
What do you mean?

00:21:11.041 --> 00:21:12.751
He looked like he knew everything.

00:21:13.252 --> 00:21:15.796
I didn't tell him you killed Hwang.

00:21:16.755 --> 00:21:19.091
Like we agreed,

00:21:19.717 --> 00:21:22.011
I just said he died in a fire.

00:21:22.845 --> 00:21:24.680
Which is true. He did die in a fire.

00:21:26.974 --> 00:21:28.058
Well, doesn't matter.

00:21:29.101 --> 00:21:30.603
He didn't really seem to care.

00:21:31.312 --> 00:21:32.313
Yeah?

00:21:33.063 --> 00:21:34.940
But how did Jang Geonyoung know?

00:21:40.112 --> 00:21:41.655
We got a rat or what?

00:21:56.086 --> 00:21:57.254
Did you find Baek Kitae?

00:21:58.088 --> 00:21:59.590
He's nowhere to be found.

00:21:59.673 --> 00:22:01.216
He hasn't been home,

00:22:01.300 --> 00:22:03.761
and the KCIA's keeping their mouths shut.

00:22:05.721 --> 00:22:07.139
What about the scene?

00:22:07.222 --> 00:22:09.099
All we found were some bullet casings.

00:22:09.183 --> 00:22:10.851
Everything burned to a crisp.

00:22:10.935 --> 00:22:12.186
There's no evidence left.

00:22:15.564 --> 00:22:19.151
But, sir, is it really
okay for us to keep doing this here…

00:22:19.234 --> 00:22:23.280
I mean, there's nothing left to dig into,

00:22:23.364 --> 00:22:25.783
and if the deputy chief finds out,
he'll rip into us.

00:22:25.866 --> 00:22:27.117
What about Kang Daeil?

00:22:27.618 --> 00:22:29.536
Any word from him?

00:22:37.795 --> 00:22:42.007
When are the materials
from Japan getting here?

