00:35:47.375 --> 00:35:48.543
Think, for God's sake.

00:35:49.836 --> 00:35:51.796
Baek's got Chief Cheon backing him.

00:35:51.880 --> 00:35:53.089
Who have you got?

00:35:53.173 --> 00:35:56.676
If you're going to go after them,
you've got to match their weight at least!

00:35:56.760 --> 00:35:58.636
You complete idiot.

00:36:05.477 --> 00:36:09.063
"The Prosecution,
walking the straight path,

00:36:09.147 --> 00:36:10.648
upholding principle!"

00:36:24.746 --> 00:36:25.872
Hey, get back inside.

00:36:29.250 --> 00:36:30.585
You too. Get back inside.

00:36:39.427 --> 00:36:42.680
Hope you don't mind me
calling you in while I do this.

00:36:43.556 --> 00:36:45.725
I've got to take good care
of the President,

00:36:45.809 --> 00:36:48.561
but I never get time to hit the field.

00:36:49.395 --> 00:36:50.396
Not at all, sir.

00:36:50.939 --> 00:36:52.607
Don't worry about it.

00:36:54.150 --> 00:36:59.197
I hear Chief Cheon's been meddling
with prosecutorial authority?

00:36:59.280 --> 00:37:00.281
Yes, sir.

00:37:01.074 --> 00:37:02.659
It seems he ordered the KCIA

00:37:02.742 --> 00:37:04.994
to investigate
Director Hwang's case directly.

00:37:18.842 --> 00:37:20.093
Go on.

00:37:20.176 --> 00:37:21.469
The truth is,

00:37:21.553 --> 00:37:23.555
one of our prosecutors
in the Narcotics Unit

00:37:24.055 --> 00:37:25.765
was investigating Baek Kitae,

00:37:25.849 --> 00:37:29.185
the KCIA department head who's in charge
of Hwang's case right now,

00:37:29.269 --> 00:37:30.854
for running a meth operation.

00:37:31.771 --> 00:37:34.732
I know it's presumptuous of me
to say this to you,

00:37:35.900 --> 00:37:38.695
but the fact that the Chief
of the Presidential Security Service

00:37:38.778 --> 00:37:41.155
- would back someone like Baek--
- Chief Cheon is

00:37:41.948 --> 00:37:44.534
covering for a meth peddler?

00:37:55.169 --> 00:37:59.549
OSAKA, JAPAN

00:38:06.097 --> 00:38:08.016
Looks like I'm the last one.

00:38:08.099 --> 00:38:10.727
I'm sorry to keep you waiting, Father.

00:38:11.769 --> 00:38:12.854
So,

00:38:13.813 --> 00:38:15.690
how many factories do we have left?

00:38:17.775 --> 00:38:21.613
We've still got a couple left,
but the police are watching them closely.

00:38:22.530 --> 00:38:24.741
There's no telling how long they'll last.

00:38:24.824 --> 00:38:27.702
Everyone says the meth trade's
finished in Japan.

00:38:27.785 --> 00:38:31.164
Even the Shibazaki clan seems
to be pulling out of the business.

00:38:31.247 --> 00:38:32.248
Finished? Hardly.

00:38:32.832 --> 00:38:36.836
Addicts are still crawling
all over Japan looking for drugs.

00:38:38.212 --> 00:38:41.049
We just need to build
a new plant in Korea,

00:38:41.132 --> 00:38:43.843
and the problem's solved, Father.

00:38:44.636 --> 00:38:48.348
In Korea, we can easily bring in
raw materials from Hong Kong or Taiwan,

00:38:48.431 --> 00:38:50.224
and enforcement is weak.

00:38:52.352 --> 00:38:55.480
It's the ideal place to produce meth.

00:38:56.064 --> 00:39:02.528
Look, just when is this new plant
supposed to be built?

00:39:03.029 --> 00:39:08.326
Chasing pipe dreams like a fool
only puts the clan at risk.

00:39:09.494 --> 00:39:12.288
The meth market grows every year,

00:39:12.372 --> 00:39:15.166
and it's still
our biggest source of funds.

00:39:16.459 --> 00:39:18.795
Giving that up too easily

00:39:20.088 --> 00:39:22.799
is what would put the clan at risk.

00:39:24.509 --> 00:39:26.552
The real foolishness, don't you think?

00:39:26.636 --> 00:39:29.681
You're forgetting your place,
you Chosenjin!

00:39:30.515 --> 00:39:31.849
How dare you!

00:39:43.277 --> 00:39:44.362
I hope

00:39:45.822 --> 00:39:48.741
you're not making a foolish choice.

00:39:50.034 --> 00:39:53.121
Because giving a fool a chance is

00:39:53.830 --> 00:39:55.331
just as foolish.

00:40:17.854 --> 00:40:21.983
SEOUL, KOREA

00:40:26.195 --> 00:40:28.823
Seems like you've taken
quite a liking to Baek Kitae.

00:40:28.906 --> 00:40:31.242
You forgave him
for taking out Director Hwang.

00:40:32.035 --> 00:40:34.162
He's the one who killed Hwang?

00:40:34.662 --> 00:40:35.955
You didn't know?

00:40:36.039 --> 00:40:37.832
I heard he died in a fire.

00:40:38.332 --> 00:40:39.667
Am I mistaken?

